<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idef865e91-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s2582"><num value="2582">§ 2582.</num><heading> Severability</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">If this chapter is held unconstitutional as to some provisions or circumstances, it shall remain in force as to the remaining provisions and other circumstances.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idef865e92-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/pl/91/577/tIII/s132">Pub. L. 91–577, title III, § 132</ref>, <date date="1970-12-24">Dec. 24, 1970</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/84/1558">84 Stat. 1558</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
